38 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
39 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
40 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
41 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
42 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
43 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
44  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
45 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
46 #else
47 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
48 #endif
49 #endif
50 
51 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
52 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
53 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
54 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
55 #else
56 #error "unknown compiler"
57 #endif
58 
59 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
60 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
61 #else
62 #include <cstdio>
63 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
64  do { \
65  fputs(msg, stderr); \
66  DNNL_TRAP(); \
67  } while (0)
68 #endif

84 struct error : public std::exception {
85  dnnl_status_t status;
86  const char *message;
87 
92  error(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message)
93  : status(status), message(message) {}
94 
96  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
97 
103  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
104  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
105  }
106 };
107 
109 template <typename T>
110 void validate_container_size(const T &v, const char *error_message,
111  int min_size = 1, int max_size = -1) {
112  const int size = (int)v.size();
113  if (size < min_size || (max_size >= 0 && size > max_size))
114  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, error_message);
115 }
117 
119 template <typename T>
120 struct handle_traits {};
121 
135 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
136 struct handle {
137 private:
138  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
139  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> data_ {0};
140 
141 protected:
142  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == data_.get(); }
143  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
144 
145 public:
153  handle() = default;
154 
156  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
158  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
160  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
162  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
163 
169  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
170 
176  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
177  data_.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
178  }
179 
185  T get(bool allow_empty = false) const {
186  T result = data_.get();
187  if (allow_empty == false && result == nullptr)
188  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(
189  dnnl_invalid_arguments, "object is not initialized");
190  return result;
191  }
192 
197  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
198 
202  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
203 
210  bool operator==(const handle<T, traits> &other) const {
211  return other.data_.get() == data_.get();
212  }
213 
220  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
221 };

375 dnnl::primitive::kind primitive::get_kind() const {
376  const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = get_primitive_desc();
377  // TODO (Roma): the code below is only needed because get_primitive_desc
378  // returns a C type.
379  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
380  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
381  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
382  "could not get a primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
383  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
384 }

674 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
675  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
676  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
677  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
678  } \
679 \
680  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
681  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
682  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
683  } \
684 \
685  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
686  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
687  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
688  } \
689 \
690  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
691  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
692  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
693  return lhs; \
694  } \
695 \
696  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
697  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
698  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
699  return lhs; \
700  } \
701 \
702  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
703  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
704  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
705  return lhs; \
706  } \
707 \
708  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
709  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
710  }
711 
712 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
713 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)

873 struct engine : public handle<dnnl_engine_t> {
874  friend struct primitive;
875  friend struct reorder;
876 
878  enum class kind {
880  any = dnnl_any_engine,
882  cpu = dnnl_cpu,
884  gpu = dnnl_gpu,
885  };
886 
887  using handle::handle;
888 
891  engine() = default;
892 
897  static size_t get_count(kind akind) {
898  return dnnl_engine_get_count(convert_to_c(akind));
899  }
900 
906  engine(kind akind, size_t index) {
907  dnnl_engine_t engine;
908  error::wrap_c_api(
909  dnnl_engine_create(&engine, convert_to_c(akind), index),
910  "could not create an engine");
911  reset(engine);
912  }
913 
918  engine(const handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> &pd) {
919  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
920  error::wrap_c_api(
921  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
922  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &c_engine),
923  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
924  reset(c_engine, true);
925  }
926 
929  kind get_kind() const {
930  dnnl_engine_kind_t kind;
931  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_kind(get(), &kind),
932  "could not get kind of an engine");
933  return static_cast<engine::kind>(kind);
934  }
935 
941  template <typename primitive_desc>
942  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
943  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
944  }
945 
946 private:
947  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind akind) {
948  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(akind);
949  }
950 
951  template <typename primitive_desc>
952  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
953  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
954  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
955  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &c_engine),
956  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
957  return engine(c_engine, true);
958  }
959 };

989 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
990  using handle::handle;
991 
993  enum class flags : unsigned {
995  in_order = dnnl_stream_in_order,
997  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
999  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1000  };
1001 
1004  stream() = default;
1005 
1011  stream(const engine &aengine, flags aflags = flags::default_flags) {
1012  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1013  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create(&stream, aengine.get(),
1014  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(aflags)),
1015  "could not create a stream");
1016  reset(stream);
1017  }
1018 
1020  engine get_engine() const {
1021  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
1022  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_engine(get(), &c_engine),
1023  "could not get an engine from a stream object");
1024  return engine(c_engine, true);
1025  }
1026 
1029  stream &wait() {
1030  error::wrap_c_api(
1031  dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait on a stream");
1032  return *this;
1033  }
1034 };

1986 
1988  struct desc {
1989  friend struct memory;
1991  dnnl_memory_desc_t data;
1992 
1995  desc() : data() {}
1996 
2012  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, format_tag aformat_tag,
2013  bool allow_empty = false)
2014  : data() {
2015  validate_dims(adims);
2016  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data,
2017  (int)adims.size(), adims.data(), convert_to_c(adata_type),
2018  convert_to_c(aformat_tag));
2019  if (!allow_empty)
2020  error::wrap_c_api(status,
2021  "could not construct a memory descriptor using a "
2022  "format tag");
2023  }
2024 
2040  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, const dims &strides,
2041  bool allow_empty = false)
2042  : data() {
2043  validate_dims(adims);
2044  if (!strides.empty()) validate_dims(strides, (int)adims.size());
2045  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data,
2046  (int)adims.size(), adims.data(), convert_to_c(adata_type),
2047  strides.empty() ? nullptr : &strides[0]);
2048  if (!allow_empty)
2049  error::wrap_c_api(status,
2050  "could not construct a memory descriptor using "
2051  "strides");
2052  }
2053 
2057  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &data) : data(data) {}
2058 
2061  //
2070  desc submemory_desc(const dims &adims, const dims &offsets,
2071  bool allow_empty = false) const {
2072  validate_dims(adims, data.ndims);
2073  validate_dims(offsets, data.ndims);
2074  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
2075  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
2076  &sub_md, &data, adims.data(), offsets.data());
2077  if (!allow_empty)
2078  error::wrap_c_api(status, "could not construct a sub-memory");
2079  return desc(sub_md);
2080  }
2081 
2126  desc reshape(const dims &adims, bool allow_empty = false) const {
2127  if (data.ndims) validate_dims(adims, 1);
2128  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
2129  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_reshape(
2130  &out_md, &data, (int)adims.size(), adims.data());
2131  if (!allow_empty)
2132  error::wrap_c_api(
2133  status, "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
2134  return desc(out_md);
2135  }
2136 
2174  desc permute_axes(const std::vector<int> &permutation,
2175  bool allow_empty = false) const {
2176  validate_dims(permutation, data.ndims);
2177  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
2178  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_permute_axes(
2179  &out_md, &data, permutation.data());
2180  if (!allow_empty)
2181  error::wrap_c_api(status,
2182  "could not permute axes of a memory descriptor");
2183  return desc(out_md);
2184  }
2185 
2190  memory::dims dims() const {

3274  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
3275  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
3276  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
3277  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
3278  query::exec_arg_md};
3279  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
3280  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
3281  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3282  "memory descriptor query is invalid");
3283 
3284  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
3285  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
3286  return cdesc ? memory::desc(*cdesc) : memory::desc();
3287  }

3401  engine scratchpad_engine() const {
3402  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
3403  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(get(),
3404  dnnl::convert_to_c(query::scratchpad_engine),
3405  0, &c_engine),
3406  "could not retrieve scratchpad engine from a primitive "
3407  "descriptor");
3408  return engine(c_engine, true);
3409  }
3410 
3413  primitive_attr get_primitive_attr() const {
3414  const_dnnl_primitive_attr_t const_c_attr;
3415  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_get_attr(get(), &const_c_attr),
3416  "could not get attributes from a primitive descriptor");
3417  dnnl_primitive_attr_t c_attr;
3418  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_clone(&c_attr, const_c_attr),
3419  "could not clone primitive attributes");
3420  return primitive_attr(c_attr);
3421  }
3422 
3425  dnnl::primitive::kind get_kind() const {
3426  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
3427  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(get(),
3428  dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
3429  "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
3430  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
3431  }
3432 
3433 protected:
3437  void reset_with_clone(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd) {
3438  dnnl_primitive_desc_t new_pd;
3439  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_clone(&new_pd, pd),
3440  "could not clone a primitive descriptor");
3441  reset(new_pd);
3442  }
3443 
3457  primitive_desc_base(
3458  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
3459  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
3460 
3472  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3473  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind aprop_kind)
3474  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, aprop_kind, aprop_kind) {}
3475 
3489  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
3490  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
3491  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
3492  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
3493  if (pd == nullptr) return;
3494 
3495  dnnl_status_t rc;
3496 
3497  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
3498  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
3499  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
3500 
3501  // Check that primitive kind matches
3502  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
3503  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3504  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
3505  error::wrap_c_api(
3506  rc, "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
3507  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
3508  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3509  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
3510 
3511  // Check that propagation kind matches
3512  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
3513  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
3514  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
3515 
3516  // Something went wrong
3517  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
3518  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3519  "could not get propagation kind from the primitive "
3520  "descriptor");
3521 
3522  // Everything is fine
3523  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
3524  || (rc == dnnl_success
3525  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
3526  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
3527  reset_with_clone(pd);
3528  return;
3529  }
3530 
3531  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
3532  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
3533  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
3534  }
3535 
3536  using base = primitive_desc_base;
3537 };

3576  primitive_desc(const engine &src_engine, const memory::desc &src_md,

3589  }

3609  &src_md.data, src.get_engine().get(), &dst_md.data,
3610  dst.get_engine().get(), attr.get());
3611  if (!allow_empty)
3612  error::wrap_c_api(status,

3616  }

3635  }

3639 
3641  memory::desc dst_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(0); }
3642  };

3660  : primitive(primitive_desc(src, dst, attr).get()) {}

3662  using primitive::execute;

3684 
3686 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
3687  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
3688  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_mems;
3689  c_mems.reserve(mems.size());
3690  for (const auto &s : mems)
3691  c_mems.push_back(s.data);
3692  return c_mems;
3693 }

3883 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
3884  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
3885 
3886  primitive_desc() = default;
3887 
3910  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
3911  const engine &aengine, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
3912  bool allow_empty = false)
3913  : allow_empty_(allow_empty) {
3914  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
3915  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
3916  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, aengine.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
3917  if (!allow_empty)
3918  error::wrap_c_api(
3919  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
3920  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
3921  fetch_impl();
3922  }
3923 
3928  bool next_impl() {
3929  dnnl_status_t status
3930  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
3931  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
3932  error::wrap_c_api(
3933  status, "could not advance a primitive descriptor iterator");
3934  fetch_impl();
3935  return true;
3936  }
3937 
3938 private:
3939  bool allow_empty_ = false;
3940  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
3941  void fetch_impl() {
3942  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
3943  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty_));
3944  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty_ ? dnnl_success
3945  : dnnl_out_of_memory,
3946  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from a primitive "
3947  "descriptor iterator");
3948  reset(pd);
3949  }
3950 };

7539  }

7598  return base::query_md(query::exec_arg_md, DNNL_ARG_DIFF_DST_ITER_C);
7599  }
7600 
7601 protected:
7602  using rnn_base = rnn_primitive_desc_base;
7603 
7604  // (Deliberately not using doxygen comments)
7605  //
7606  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor base from a C API primitive
7607  // descriptor while checking that it actually describes the expected
7608  // primitive by comparing propagation and primitive kinds. Caller can
7609  // pass two options propagation kinds. This is typically used to check
7610  // that propagation kind is inference or training forward propagation.
7611  //
7612  // @param pd C API primitive descriptor.
7613  // @param prop_kind1 Expected propagation kind.
7614  // @param prop_kind2 Expected propagation kind.
7615  // @param cell_kind Expected cell kind.
7616  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
7617  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
7618  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
7619  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
7620  dnnl_status_t rc;
7621  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
7622  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
7623  "could not retrieve a descriptor from a primitive descriptor "
7624  "for an RNN primitive");
7625 
7626  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
7627  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
7628  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
7629 
7630  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
7631  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
7632  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
7633  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
7634 
7635  if (!ok)
7636  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
7637  "mismatch between expected and provided descriptors for an "
7638  "RNN primitive");
7639 
7640  reset_with_clone(pd);
7641  }
7642 };

7645 struct vanilla_rnn_forward : public primitive {

7649 
7690  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm activation,
7691  rnn_direction direction, const memory::desc &src_layer_desc,
7692  const memory::desc &src_iter_desc,
7693  const memory::desc &weights_layer_desc,
7694  const memory::desc &weights_iter_desc,
7695  const memory::desc &bias_desc,
7696  const memory::desc &dst_layer_desc,
7697  const memory::desc &dst_iter_desc,
7698  rnn_flags flags = rnn_flags::undef, float alpha = 0.0f,
7699  float beta = 0.0f) {
7700  error::wrap_c_api(
7701  dnnl_vanilla_rnn_forward_desc_init(&data,
7702  dnnl::convert_to_c(aprop_kind),
7703  dnnl::convert_to_c(activation),
7704  dnnl::convert_to_c(direction), &src_layer_desc.data,
7705  &src_iter_desc.data, &weights_layer_desc.data,
7706  &weights_iter_desc.data, &bias_desc.data,
7707  &dst_layer_desc.data, &dst_iter_desc.data,
7708  dnnl::convert_to_c(flags), alpha, beta),
7709  "could not create a descriptor for a vanilla RNN forward "

7810 
7863  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm activation,
7864  rnn_direction direction, const memory::desc &src_layer_desc,

7884  dnnl::convert_to_c(direction), &src_layer_desc.data,
7885  &src_iter_desc.data, &weights_layer_desc.data,
7886  &weights_iter_desc.data, &bias_desc.data,
7887  &dst_layer_desc.data, &dst_iter_desc.data,
7888  &diff_src_layer_desc.data, &diff_src_iter_desc.data,
7889  &diff_weights_layer_desc.data,
7890  &diff_weights_iter_desc.data, &diff_bias_desc.data,
7891  &diff_dst_layer_desc.data, &diff_dst_iter_desc.data,
7892  dnnl::convert_to_c(flags), alpha, beta),
7893  "could not create a descriptor for a vanilla RNN backward "
7894  "propagation primitive");
7895  }
7896  };

9968 struct resampling_forward : public primitive {
9970  struct desc {
9971  dnnl_resampling_desc_t data;
9972 
9988  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm aalgorithm,
9989  const memory::desc &src_desc, const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
9990  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
9991  dnnl::convert_to_c(aprop_kind),
9992  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), nullptr,
9993  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
9994  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
9995  }
9996 
10008  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm aalgorithm,
10009  const std::vector<float> &factors,
10010  const memory::desc &src_desc) {
10011  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
10012  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
10013  dnnl::convert_to_c(aprop_kind),
10014  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), &factors[0],
10015  &src_desc.data, nullptr),
10016  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
10017  }
10018 
10035  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm aalgorithm,
10036  const std::vector<float> &factors, const memory::desc &src_desc,
10037  const memory::desc &dst_desc) {
10038  if (!factors.empty())
10039  memory::validate_dims(factors, src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
10040  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_forward_desc_init(&data,
10041  dnnl::convert_to_c(aprop_kind),
10042  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), factors.data(),
10043  &src_desc.data, &dst_desc.data),
10044  "could not create a resampling forward descriptor");
10045  }
10046  };

10143  const memory::desc &diff_src_desc,
10144  const memory::desc &diff_dst_desc) {
10145  if (!factors.empty())
10146  memory::validate_dims(factors, diff_src_desc.data.ndims - 2);
10147  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_backward_desc_init(&data,
10148  convert_to_c(aalgorithm), factors.data(),
10149  &diff_src_desc.data, &diff_dst_desc.data),
10150  "could not create a resampling backward data descriptor");
10151  }
10152  };

10954 inline primitive::primitive(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t c_pd) {

10962 
10963 inline void primitive::execute(const stream &astream,
10964  const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
10965  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
10966  c_args.reserve(args.size());
10967  for (const auto &a : args)
10968  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get(true)});
10969 
10970  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), astream.get(),
10971  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
10972  "could not execute a primitive");
10973 }
